# Moussawer — Agent Rules & Context

## Stack

- **Runtime:** Node.js (v22+), TypeScript
- **Backend:** Express + Prisma Client + Zod + JWT
- **Frontend:** React 19 + Vite + React Router v7 + plain CSS
- **Database:** SQLite (via Prisma ORM)
- **Testing:** Vitest + Supertest
- **API docs:** OpenAPI (swagger-ui-express)

## Project Structure

```
moussawer/
├── server/            # Express API
│   ├── index.ts       # Entry point
│   ├── app.ts         # Express app setup
│   ├── config.ts      # Env config
│   ├── db.ts          # Prisma client
│   ├── openapi.ts     # OpenAPI spec
│   ├── middleware/     # Auth, error handling
│   ├── routes/        # API route handlers
│   ├── services/      # Business logic (availability, notifications, resources)
│   └── utils/         # HTTP helpers
├── src/               # React frontend
│   ├── App.tsx
│   ├── components/    # UI components
│   ├── contexts/      # Auth context
│   ├── lib/           # API client
│   └── pages/         # Route pages
├── prisma/
│   ├── schema.prisma  # Database schema (single source of truth)
│   ├── seed.ts        # Seed data
│   └── dev.db         # SQLite database file
├── tests/
│   └── api.test.ts    # API integration tests
└── docs/              # Project documentation
```

## Key Commands

```bash
npm run dev        # API + web dev servers
npm run dev:api    # API only
npm run dev:web    # Vite only
npm run db:reset   # Rebuild SQLite schema and seed data
npm test           # Reset DB and run API integration tests
npm run lint       # ESLint
npm run build      # TypeScript check + production frontend build
```

## Database

- SQLite via Prisma ORM (provider: `sqlite`)
- Schema source of truth: `prisma/schema.prisma`
- DB file: `prisma/dev.db`
- `npm run db:push` uses SQL generation workaround: `prisma migrate diff --from-empty --to-schema-datamodel ... | sqlite3`
- Models: User, ClientProfile, PhotographerProfile, Category, PhotographerCategory, PhotographerService, AvailabilityRule, CalendarBlock, PortfolioItem, Booking, Conversation, ConversationParticipant, Message, Incident, Dispute, DisputeComment, Review, Favorite, Notification, ActivityLog

## Conventions

- **API:** All endpoints under `/api/v1`
- **Auth:** JWT bearer tokens (`Authorization: Bearer <token>`)
- **Response shape:** `{ data }` or `{ data, meta }` for success, `{ error: { code, message, details } }` for errors
- **Error codes:** `VALIDATION_ERROR` (422), `SLOT_UNAVAILABLE` (409), `BOOKING_CONFLICT` (409), `INVALID_STATUS_TRANSITION` (422)
- **Roles:** `ADMIN`, `CLIENT`, `PHOTOGRAPHER`
- **Status enums:** `AccountStatus` (ACTIVE/SUSPENDED/DISABLED), `BookingStatus` (PENDING/CONFIRMED/COMPLETED/CANCELLED), `IncidentStatus` (OPEN/UNDER_REVIEW/RESOLVED/CLOSED), `DisputeStatus` (OPEN/AWAITING_RESPONSE/UNDER_REVIEW/RESOLVED/REJECTED/CLOSED)
- **Naming:** camelCase in TypeScript, snake_case in DB
- **Validation:** Zod schemas in services/routes
- **Testing:** Vitest + Supertest, DB reset before each test run

## Test Accounts

```
admin@example.com / password
photographer-one@example.com / password
photographer-two@example.com / password
photographer-three@example.com / password
client@example.com / password
```

## Development Workflow

1. Always read existing files before changing them
2. Run `npm run db:reset` before testing to ensure clean state
3. Run `npm test` before committing
4. Run `npm run lint` to check code style
5. Keep OpenAPI spec (`server/openapi.ts`) in sync with routes

## Known Limitations

- Prisma `db push` engine fails in this environment; SQL workaround used
- Timezone handling needs hardening before production
- Image uploads are URL-based placeholders
- Payments/refunds are placeholders
- Real-time messaging not implemented (polling-based)
- Admin moderation UI is intentionally minimal
